{"word":"οἰοπόλος","slug":"οἰοπόλος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>οἰοπόλος</b></el> <el>(οἰο-πόλος, ον,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>οἶς, πολέω</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>traversed by sheep</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>lonely, solitary, single</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>tending sheep</i>, <b>Hhymn.</b><p/></div>"}]}